<file path="README.md">
# Festen St Michel de l'Attalaye

Offline-first PWA for the 2026 St Michel Smart City Festival.

**Stack:** SvelteKit · TypeScript · Tailwind · Cloudflare Pages · D1 · KV · OPFS SQLite · WebAuthn

---

## ⚡ Quick start (read me first)

```bash
pnpm install
pnpm setup        # ← THIS RUNS MIGRATIONS. Without it, every API returns 500.
pnpm dev          # http://localhost:5173
```

That's it. `pnpm setup` runs all 11 migrations against the local
Miniflare D1 database. `pnpm dev` then starts SvelteKit with the
Cloudflare adapter's `platformProxy` providing real D1 + KV
bindings — full production parity, no separate `wrangler` process
needed.

If you skip `pnpm setup`, the app loads but every server endpoint
returns HTTP 503 with the message `dev_d1_not_migrated`. Look in
the dev console for a giant red banner pointing at the fix.

---

## First-time admin setup

After running `pnpm setup`, the local D1 contains an empty
`admin_allowlist` table seeded with one bootstrap row: `admin`.
Either:

- **Use the bootstrap password** (set in `.env`):
  - go to <http://localhost:5173/admin/login>
  - Method: "Use password"
  - Mode: "Login"
  - Username: `admin`, Password: `festival-lakay-dev`

- **Or register a passkey:**
  - go to <http://localhost:5173/admin/login>
  - Method: passkey, Mode: register
  - Username: `admin` (must match an `admin_allowlist` row)
  - Follow the browser's passkey prompt

For production you MUST replace the bootstrap row:

```bash
wrangler d1 execute stmichel-festival-db --remote --command "DELETE FROM admin_allowlist WHERE username='admin'"
wrangler d1 execute stmichel-festival-db --remote --command "INSERT INTO admin_allowlist (username, note, added_by) VALUES ('real-admin-name', 'Phone: ...', 'system')"
```

---

## Production deploy

```bash
# One-time:
wrangler d1 create stmichel-festival-db          # paste UUID into wrangler.toml
wrangler kv:namespace create KV                  # paste ID into wrangler.toml
pnpm db:migrate                                  # runs all 11 migrations against production D1

# Every deploy:
pnpm build
pnpm deploy
pnpm verify                                      # post-deploy smoke test
```

Set the following in **Cloudflare Pages → Settings → Environment variables → Production**:

| Variable | Value |
|----------|-------|
| `PUBLIC_RP_ID` | your production hostname (e.g. `stmichel.ht`) |
| `WHATSAPP_VERIFY_TOKEN` | from Meta App Dashboard |
| `WHATSAPP_PHONE_ID` | from Meta App Dashboard |
| `WHATSAPP_TOKEN` | from Meta App Dashboard |
| `WHATSAPP_APP_SECRET` | from Meta App Dashboard → Basic Settings |
| `ADMIN_BOOTSTRAP_PASSWORD` | (optional) leave unset to disable password fallback |

---

## Two dev modes

| Command | What it does | When to use |
|---------|--------------|-------------|
| `pnpm dev` | Vite dev server with platformProxy → real Miniflare D1+KV | 99% of dev work |
| `pnpm dev:wrangler` | Build, then `wrangler pages dev` against the build | Test the actual production worker bundle |

You'll usually only ever use `pnpm dev`.

---

## Testing

```bash
pnpm test              # 248+ tests, ~3s
pnpm test:watch        # watch mode
pnpm check             # svelte-check + TypeScript
```

The suite is standalone — no browser, no Playwright. Tests pass
without `node_modules` for `svelte-check` because the runner
mocks the build chain.

---

## Tile download (offline maps)

```bash
pnpm tiles:download    # ~40 MB, OSM tiles for zoom 13–16 around St Michel
```

Populates `static/map-tiles/`. Required for `/map` to render
offline; optional for online use.

---

## Replace placeholder assets before launch

`static/icon-192.png`, `static/icon-512.png`, and
`static/og-default.jpg` are currently solid Haitian-blue
placeholders generated at build time. Swap them with real
branded artwork before public launch. The PWA install prompt
and Open Graph share previews will look much better.


---

## Admin management (Round 12)

### Demo login

Visit `/admin/login` and click **"Gade demo (read-only)"**. You get a
session as user `demo` that can SEE every admin page. Every mutating
endpoint returns 403, so you can't accidentally write to real festival
data. Disabled in production unless `ADMIN_DEMO_ENABLED=1`.

### Engineer grants an admin

The fastest way to give someone admin access:

```bash
# Approve them (they'll register their own credential)
node scripts/grant-admin.js alice@example.com

# OR pre-set a password they can change after first login
node scripts/grant-admin.js bob@example.com 'temporary-password-123'

# Run against production D1
node scripts/grant-admin.js carol@example.com 'pw' --remote
```

The hashing happens locally. The cleartext password never leaves
your machine — only the salted PBKDF2 hash is sent to D1.

### Admins manage other admins

Existing admins can review pending requests at
`/admin/dashboard/admins`. Anyone can request access via a public
form (POST to `/admin/api/request-access`); existing admins approve
or reject from the dashboard.

### Demo content

Migration 013 seeds 4 demo events, 4 POIs, 2 history items, 2 matches
(one with a score), and 2 photo albums. All have slugs starting
with `demo-`. Clear them before launch:

```bash
pnpm demo:clear           # production
# or just run the SQL manually
```

The OG default image (`/og-default.jpg`) is a Haitian-blue placeholder.
Replace it with real branded artwork before launch.
</file>

<file path="scripts/copy-wasm.js">
import { copyFileSync, mkdirSync } from 'fs';

const dir = '.svelte-kit/cloudflare/_app/immutable/workers';
const src = 'node_modules/.pnpm/@sqlite.org+sqlite-wasm@3.53.0-build1/node_modules/@sqlite.org/sqlite-wasm/dist';

mkdirSync(dir, { recursive: true });
copyFileSync(`${src}/sqlite3.wasm`, `${dir}/sqlite3.wasm`);
copyFileSync(`${src}/sqlite3-opfs-async-proxy.js`, `${dir}/sqlite3-opfs-async-proxy.js`);
console.log('✅ sqlite3.wasm + opfs proxy copied to workers dir');
